
[1]saxifrage

   SAX'IFRAGE, n. [L. saqxifraga; composed of saxum, a stone, and frango,
   to break.]

   A medicine that has the property of breaking or dissolving the stone in
   the bladder. But in botany, a genus of plants of many species. The
   burnet saxifrage is of the genus Pimpinella; the golden saxifrage is of
   the genus Chrysoplenium; the meadow saxifrage is of the genus
   Peucedanum.
